---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, '/');
---
<section id="podcast" aria-label="Podcasting and content creation" class="section">

  <div class="sec-body-grid">
    <div class="sec-left">

      <div class="sec-meta">
        <span class="sec-date">2020 — present</span>
        <span class="sec-company">Independent</span>
        <span class="sec-industry">Tech · Writing</span>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-q">"How do others do this?"</p>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Podcasting</h2>
      <p class="sec-sub">The Manu&lt;script&gt; — exploring the intersection between writing and technology.</p>

      <div class="sec-stats">
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">30</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">episodes</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">7+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">countries represented</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-text">In 2020, tech writing was just starting to surface as a career in Brazil, and I had a question I couldn't answer alone: if what we're doing is called tech writing, how do others actually do it? What can we learn from them to scale what we build? So a colleague and I started a podcast. It quickly expanded beyond tech writers to anyone living at the intersection of writing and technology. The Manu&lt;script&gt; became a way to reach professionals across contexts and companies I'd never otherwise access — and to create something of value in exchange for their time. Every episode forced me to deeply research a person's career, industry, and role before we spoke, to understand what they specifically could teach me that no one else could. Interviewing, it turns out, is its own discipline.</p>
      <div class="sec-links">
        <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/3fxF61LYR4BBDAv6YhZV5r" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Manuscript on Spotify ↗</a>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="sec-panels">
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Skills</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill">Podcast Production</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Interview Research</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Content Strategy</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Storytelling</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Audience Development</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Community Engagement</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Tools</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Spotify</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Descript</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Anchor</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case card row — full width below the 2-col grid -->
  <div class="sec-cases-row">
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-img">
        <img src={`${base}images/cases/daily-pmm.png`} alt="Daily PMM" />
      </div>
      <div class="sec-case-type">Independent podcast · PMM education</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">Daily PMM</h3>
      <a href="#" class="sec-case-link">View project ↗</a>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-img">
        <img src={`${base}images/cases/manuscript.png`} alt="The Manuscript" />
      </div>
      <div class="sec-case-type">Independent podcast · Tech &amp; Writing</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">The Manu&lt;script&gt;</h3>
      <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/3fxF61LYR4BBDAv6YhZV5r" class="sec-case-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Listen on Spotify ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
